Today, a BBC spokesman confirmed Mr Lowe's show was recorded in advance, but it was categorised as a 'low risk'.

Mr Lowe told The Telegraph he would record his shows six days before they were due to be broadcast.

He described how he would upload the audio along with the compliance forms to the station's internal system well in advance.

Mr Lowe says the system requires a broadcaster to nominate someone in BBC management to listen to the show.

